re</a> to see how to calculate
  the area of a pentagon.</td></tr>

<tr><td><h7><b>Volume</b></h7></td></tr>
<tr><td>The dodecahedron is made up of 12 pyramids with pentagon as the bas=
e.<br>
  <a href=3D"https://personal.math.ubc.ca/~cass/courses/m308/projects/cchan=
g/webpages/ps/dodeca-pyramid.ps"><img src=3D"https://personal.math.ubc.ca/~=
cass/courses/m308/projects/cchang/webpages/pictures/dodeca-pyramid.JPG"></a=
><br>
  The volume of one pyramid =3D (base area =D7 height) /3 =3D 12 =D7 the vo=
lume of pyramid.<br>
  To calculate the height of the pyramid, use the Pythagoras theorem,<br>
  height =3D &#8730;(R=B2 - r=B2), where R is the radius of the dodecahedro=
n
  and r is the radius of each pentagon.<br>
  V =3D 15 + [(7&#8730;5) / 4]a=B3</td></tr>



